PHASE 1: PROBLEM IDENTIFICATION
Ã¢â€ &#x2019; What technical challenge does {company} face that a {current_title} with {exp} years solves?
Ã¢â€ &#x2019; Reference a REAL technology from {skills} and the SPECIFIC problem it addresses
Ã¢â€ &#x2019; Example: aging MPLS networks, security gaps, scalability bottlenecks, vendor lock-in

PHASE 2: AGITATION (why this problem matters NOW)
Ã¢â€ &#x2019; What's the cost of NOT solving it? Downtime? Security breaches? Lost revenue?
Ã¢â€ &#x2019; Make the hiring manager FEEL the urgency &#x2014; this role isn't optional, it's critical

PHASE 3: SOLUTION (why {name} is the ONLY answer)
Ã¢â€ &#x2019; Map {skills} to the problem with PRECISION &#x2014; not "experienced with networks" but "deployed MPLS across 12 sites reducing latency by 40%"
Ã¢â€ &#x2019; Use the language of someone who has DONE the work, not someone who read about it
Ã¢â€ &#x2019; Reference {certs} as proof of mastery, not as decoration

PHASE 4: ACTION (the inevitable next step)
Ã¢â€ &#x2019; Close with the quiet confidence of someone who knows their value
Ã¢â€ &#x2019; Do not ASK for an interview &#x2014; state readiness for one
Ã¢â€ &#x2019; Leave the hiring manager thinking: "If I don't call this person, my competitor will"

